<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-2958] GroovyConsole does not execute GroovyTestCase subclasses as command line invocation does</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2958</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The class&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;TestIt &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; GroovyTestCase {
    void testTrue ( ) {
        assertEquals ( 1 , 1 )
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when executed from the command line:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;|&amp;gt; ./testing.groovy
.
Time: 0.148

OK (1 test)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;but when executed in GroovyConsole:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Exception thrown: groovy.lang.MissingMethodException: No signature of method: TestIt.main() is applicable &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; argument types: ([Ljava.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;;) values: {[]}

groovy.lang.MissingMethodException: No signature of method: TestIt.main() is applicable &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; argument types: ([Ljava.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;;) values: {[]}
	at TestIt.invokeMethod(Script0)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think GroovyConsole should execute the same as command line invocation does.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
